        <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        <span class="text-neutral-800 font-medium">Bill Check by SMS</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 bg-primary-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Guides</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 ml-3">Updated June 2026</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">How to Check Bill by SMS — All DISCOs 2026 Guide</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">Not everyone has a smartphone or internet access — and even those who do sometimes prefer the simplicity of an SMS. All major Pakistani electricity and gas utilities offer <strong>SMS bill inquiry</strong> services that work on any feature phone. You simply send your 14-digit reference number (or 10-digit consumer number for gas) to the utility's SMS short code, and within 1–3 minutes you receive an SMS reply with your current bill amount and due date. This is particularly useful for senior citizens, rural consumers, and as a backup when internet access is unavailable. This guide covers the SMS codes and formats for every major Pakistani utility.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Summary: Send your 14-digit electricity reference number (or 10-digit gas consumer number) to your DISCO's SMS short code. Receive bill amount + due date within 1-3 minutes via SMS reply. Standard SMS rates apply (Rs. 1–2 per SMS). Works on any phone — no internet needed.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">SMS Bill Inquiry Codes — All Utilities</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Utility</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">SMS Code</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">What to Send</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Reply Time</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">LESCO (Lahore)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">IESCO (Islamabad)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">FESCO (Faisalabad)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">GEPCO (Gujranwala)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">MEPCO (Multan)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">PESCO (Peshawar)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">HESCO (Hyderabad)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">SEPCO (Sukkur)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">QESCO (Quetta)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">TESCO (Tribal KP)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">547</td><td class="p-3">14-digit reference number</td><td class="p-3">1–2 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">SNGPL Gas</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">8297</td><td class="p-3">10-digit consumer number</td><td class="p-3">2–3 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">SSGC Gas</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">8297</td><td class="p-3">10-digit consumer number</td><td class="p-3">2–3 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">K-Electric (Karachi)</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">N/A</td><td class="p-3">Not available — use online checker</td><td class="p-3">—</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">PTCL</td><td class="p-3 font-mono">051-111-111-111</td><td class="p-3">Send 'BILL' + phone# with area code</td><td class="p-3">2–5 min</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check LESCO Bill by SMS</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">The process is identical for all DISCOs — only the short code changes. Here's the LESCO example:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Open your phone's SMS app</strong> (Messages).</li>
      <li><strong>Compose a new SMS</strong> with your 14-digit LESCO reference number as the message body. For example: <code class="bg-neutral-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">01234567890123</code></li>
      <li><strong>Send the SMS to 547</strong>.</li>
      <li><strong>Wait 1–2 minutes</strong> for the reply.</li>
      <li><strong>You'll receive an SMS</strong> with: Consumer name, billing month, total bill amount, due date. Example reply: "LESCO Bill: Rs. 12,450, Due: 28-Jun-2026, Consumer: Muhammad Ali".</li>
      <li><strong>Save the SMS</strong> for future reference, or note the details in a paper diary.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check SNGPL Gas Bill by SMS</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">For gas bills, use the 10-digit consumer number (instead of 14-digit reference):</p>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Open your phone's SMS app.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Compose a new SMS</strong> with your 10-digit SNGPL consumer number as the message body. For example: <code class="bg-neutral-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">0123456789</code></li>
      <li><strong>Send the SMS to 8297</strong>.</li>
      <li><strong>Wait 2–3 minutes</strong> for the reply.</li>
      <li><strong>You'll receive an SMS</strong> with: Consumer name, billing month, gas bill amount, due date, units (MMBTU) consumed.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Cost of SMS Bill Inquiry</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SMS bill inquiry is <strong>not free</strong> — standard SMS rates apply. The DISCO does not charge extra, but your mobile operator's standard SMS rates apply:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Jazz:</strong> Rs. 1.50 per SMS</li>
      <li><strong>Telenor:</strong> Rs. 1.50 per SMS</li>
      <li><strong>Zong:</strong> Rs. 1.20 per SMS</li>
      <li><strong>Ufone:</strong> Rs. 1.50 per SMS</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If you have an SMS bundle (e.g., 500 SMS for Rs. 10), bill inquiry SMS counts toward your bundle — effectively free. Check with your operator for current SMS bundle options.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Common Issues & How to Resolve Them</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">No SMS reply received</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Possible causes: (1) wrong reference number entered, (2) SMS sent to wrong code (verify with table above), (3) mobile operator SMS service down, (4) DISCO SMS server down. Wait 5 minutes, try again. If still no reply, use the online checker at pakistanbill.online.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">Reply shows "Account not found"</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">You sent a wrong reference number or used a reference number from a different DISCO. Each DISCO has separate databases. Verify your DISCO and reference number from any previous bill, then try again.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">SMS reply shows old bill amount</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">SMS bill inquiry sometimes returns the last billed amount, not the current unbilled amount. If your current month's bill has not been generated yet, you'll get the previous month's amount. Check after the 15th of the month when most DISCOs generate new bills.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips for Using SMS Bill Inquiry</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Save the SMS code in your contacts</strong> — e.g., save "547" as "LESCO Bill Check" so you don't have to remember it.</li>
      <li><strong>Subscribe to an SMS bundle</strong> if you check bills frequently — Rs. 10 for 500 SMS makes each check effectively free.</li>
      <li><strong>Use SMS when internet is unavailable</strong> — works on any feature phone, even in remote areas.</li>
      <li><strong>Save the reply SMS</strong> — serves as proof of bill amount in case of dispute.</li>
      <li><strong>For K-Electric consumers</strong>: SMS inquiry is not available. Use the online checker at pakistanbill.online/k-electric-bill/ or call 118.</li>
      <li><strong>For more details</strong> (itemized charges, FPA breakdown, etc.), use the online checker — SMS only returns the summary amount.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check LESCO bill by SMS?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Send your 14-digit LESCO reference number via SMS to 547. You'll receive an SMS reply with your current bill amount and due date within 1-2 minutes. Standard SMS rates apply.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I check my electricity bill by SMS without internet?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. All major DISCOs (LESCO, IESCO, FESCO, GEPCO, MEPCO, PESCO, HESCO, SEPCO, QESCO, TESCO) offer SMS bill inquiry. Send your 14-digit reference number to the DISCO's SMS short code. Works on any phone with SMS capability — no internet needed.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is SMS bill inquiry free?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SMS bill inquiry is not free — standard SMS rates apply (Rs. 1-2 per SMS depending on your mobile operator). The DISCO does not charge extra, but your mobile operator's standard rates apply. Jazz, Telenor, Zong, and Ufone all support DISCO SMS codes.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check SNGPL gas bill by SMS?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Send your 10-digit SNGPL consumer number via SMS to 8297. You'll receive an SMS with your current gas bill amount and due date within 2-3 minutes. Standard SMS rates apply.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What SMS code do I use for K-Electric bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">K-Electric does not currently offer SMS bill inquiry. K-Electric consumers should use the online checker at pakistanbill.online/k-electric-bill/ or call K-Electric helpline 118 for bill inquiry.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Does SMS bill inquiry work on PTCL landline?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SMS bill inquiry on PTCL landline requires an SMS-enabled phone. Send 'BILL' followed by your PTCL phone number with area code to 051-111-111-111. You'll receive a return call or SMS with bill details. Alternatively, use pakistanbill.online/ptcl-bill/.</div></details>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-primary-900 mb-2">Prefer to Check Online?</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 text-sm">Online bill checking is free and gives you full bill details.</p>
      <a href="/electricity/" class="inline-block bg-primary-700 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-primary-800 transition-colors">
        Browse All Bill Checkers &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-neutral-200 pt-6">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <a href="/blog/wapda-online-bill/" class="text-sm bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-primary-700 font-semibold hover:underline">WAPDA Online Bill Guide &rarr;</a>
        <a href="/blog/how-to-find-reference-number/" class="text-sm bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-neutral-600 hover:underline">Find Reference Number &rarr;</a>
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-neutral-600 hover:underline">More Guides &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
